Object Oriented Programming(OOPs:
OOPs is just style of programing. Just a way of writing code that helps us write large amounts
of code easily. it helps us manage and change larger amounts of code. there are other
 ways as well as functional programming and procedural programming.
 Pillars os OOPs:
 there are four pillars of OOPs.
 1)Inheritance
 2)Polymorphism
 3)Abstraction
 4)Encapsulation

Classes and Objects:
A class is template/design/map/idea/blueprint from which objects are created.
